'''Akinbode Oluwafemi''' is a [[Nigerian]] [[environmental activist]], and [[tobacco control]] advocate. He is the Deputy Director of Environmental Rights Action/Friends of the Earth Nigeria (ERA/FoEN).<ref name="Today NG">{{cite news|last1=Olafimihan|first1=Kolawale|title=Investigate and sanction BAT appropriately – ERA/FoEN tells FG|url=https://www.today.ng/news/national/115159/sanction-bat-appropriately-erafoen|accessdate=15 August 2016|publisher=Today Nigeria Newspaper|date=May 2, 2016}}</ref> He is a  recipients of the 2009 Bloomberg Awards for Global Tobacco Control. The award ceremony was held at the 14th World Conference on Tobacco or Health held in [[Mumbai]], [[India]].<ref name="The Hindu">{{cite news|last1=Staff|first1=Reporter|title=Bloomberg awards announced|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/bloomberg-awards-announced/article327865.ece|accessdate=15 August 2016|publisher=The Hindu Newspaper|date=March 10, 2009}}</ref> 

